default  
default3.2
default              
defaultIn 2011, the Department of Health
default committed that it
default would explore the scope for the HCPC ‘to establish a voluntary register of [adult] social care workers [in England] by 2013’.
default3.3
default  
default              
defaultWe have
default 
defaultcare
defaultfully 
defaultconsidered this issue and concluded that there are significant shortcomings in a voluntary register being held by a statutory regulator. The
defaultse
default are
default the lack of 
defaultlegal compulsion for individuals to be registered
default and the inability of 
defaultthe regulator to demand information or 
defaultto 
defaultcompel witnesses when investigating fitness to practise allegations
default.  Crucially, it also means that if someone 
defaultwas removed from a volu
defaultntary register they could 
defaultcontinue to practis
defaulte
default. 
default3.4
default              
defaultWe 
defaultconsider
default 
defaultthe
defaultre 
defaultis 
defaultthe 
defaultpo
defaulttential for public confusion around the status of voluntary and statutory registers being held by the same organisation.
default 
defaultWe have also concluded that
default there would be considerable costs involved in establishing 
defaultsuch 
defaulta register 
defaultand paying for its operating costs until 
defaultit was 
defaultself-fin
defaultancing
default.
default3.5
default              
defaultRecent estimates are that 
defaultthe adult social care workforce 
defaultin England 
defaultnumber
defaults
default 1.63m jobs
default.
default 
defaultThis is a large, low paid and often transitory workforce with significant numbers of part time wor
defaultkers. We have concluded that ‘full statutory regulation’ 
defaultfor this group 
defaultis unlikely to be considered to be a
default 
defaultproportionate 
defaultor 
defaultcost-effecti
defaultve
default response.
default3.6
default              
defaultWe have instead proposed a ‘negative registration scheme’ and statutory regulation of CQC registered 
defaultmanagers. 
default3.7
default              
defaultA negative registration
default scheme 
defaultwould 
defaultimprove public protection because it would 
defaultenable the regulator to deal effectively with the small 
defaultnumber
default of individuals who are unsuitable to work in adult social care
default in England
default, without placing a disproportionate burden on the remainder of the workforce. 
